==English==

===Etymology===
Back conjugation of [[decaffeinated]].

===Adjective===
'''caffeinated'''

# Containing [[caffeine]] (e.g., caffeinated [[soft drinks]], [[coffee]], or [[tea]]).

===Synonyms===
regular (as in [[coffee]]); 
{slang} leaded (as in [[coffee]])

====Antonyms====
[[decaffeinated]] {also informally: [[decaf]]} (as in [[coffee]] or [[tea]]); caffeine-free (as in [[soft drinks]]); {slang} unleaded (as in [[coffee]])